The paper discusses challenges and opportunities in information retrieval, which is a core topic in computer science. The focus is on relevance feedback, which is a technique used in information retrieval. The paper also discusses the impact of new search scenarios, such as mobile phones and smart-home devices, on relevance feedback. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses user interaction with search results, which is relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
